text: A little shop serving Taiwanese delights. Surprising extent of menu, and very friendly owners. Serves a formidable array of alcoholic options. Grade A for hygiene. Definitely a gem of a find.

A simple small shop the food isn’t bad
In an old estate where I used to stay
The Chicken Just alright
Nice Hash brown through
The store owners are highly friendly and will often talk to their customers. I am generally surprised to find such a wonderful place amongst residential estates!

I bought popcorn chicken and oreo ice blended.
It was so tasty and delicious. I will definitely buy again :)
The food is delicious, but a small portion of chicken steak costs 8 Singapore dollars, which is basically a robbery. It’s so delicious that I won’t be able to come back again!
